<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-09T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-09T01:00:00-05:00" n="278" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–949: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Clark</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-09T14:00:00+08:00">April 9,
                                    1949—2 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received April 11—4:41 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Cantel 204. In April 8 meeting Canton Central Executive Committee
                            Kuomintang members present voted full support for Li Tsung-jen. Question
                            of return Generalissimo to lead opposition to Communists was not raised.
                            Resolution passed that peace negotiations should end when and if
                            Communists cross Yangtze. Participation in coalition with Communists was
                            rejected and territorial settlement with Yangtze as dividing line was
                            approved. Premier returned to Nanking to report above to Acting
                            President.</p>
                        <p>Sent Department, repeated Nanking 184, Shanghai 134.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>